parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Activation of Automatic Emergency Braking (AEB) System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the AEB system can cause sudden and unexpected braking, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or rear-end collisions, especially if there are vehicles following closely behind.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly brakes without any apparent reason
the AEB system activates with a warning message
the vehicle comes to a sudden stop
the driver experiences physical discomfort or injury due to the force of the braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning FCA sensors can cause false warnings and incorrect object detection, leading to unnecessary activation of the AEB system, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle displays false warnings of impending collisions
the FCA system incorrectly detects objects
the system shows incorrect proximity warnings
